race.comment: It's a long while since RAF ATTACK (3) won the G3 Gloaming Stakes but his last run suggested he is ready to hit that sort of form again. The run in question was the $125k Mayor's Vase over 2000m at the Gold Coast where he showed fight to be beaten just 1.1 lengths. Nicely in after Williams' claim in a BM78. Ready to break the drought. LENNOX (6) had been racing well before failing over 2400m on a heavy track at Rosehill three weeks ago. Put a line through that run. Far better placed today and maps nicely just behind the leading division. FELIX THE SCAT (2) made a move before the turn then kept finding to be beaten narrowly in the Mayor's Vase recently. Derby placegetter who is rock hard fit and capable of taking this out. CAPITAL ASSET (4) is an honest campaigner who races beyond 1800m for the first time after 36 appearances. Likely leader who can give some cheek.
